Kubernetes has more than one way to run containers in a pod. 

Two Kubernetes patterns are there:-

1. Sidecar Pattern

A secondary (helper) container that runs alongside your main application in the same Pod.

Common use cases:
- Log collection 
- Service mesh proxies (Envoy)
- Monitoring 

2. Init Container Pattern

Runs before the main application starts and must complete successfully first.

Common use cases:
- Database migrations
- Setting up configuration files.
- Config or secret setup

⚠️ The main application won't start until the init container completes successfully.

In short:
Sidecars run WITH your app.
Init Containers run BEFORE your app.
